                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d20">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A12/71a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Houghton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-10-24T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1925—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>322. Probably you have seen press statements on what President said on subject of
                    a disarmament conference. I should be glad if on your own responsibility you
                    could ascertain from the proper British authorities in such a way that it will
                    not be considered an inquiry <pb facs="0140" n="14" xml:id="pg_14"/> from this
                    Government what the attitude of that Government is toward the President’s
                    calling of such a conference and what the opinion of British officials is in
                    regard to its reception by other European countries on subjects of both land and
                    naval armament. I am not yet prepared to make inquiry of European countries and
                    for that reason wish this to be simply an informal talk by you on your own
                        responsibility.<note n="21" xml:id="d20fn21">On Oct. 26, noon, the
                        Ambassador telegraphed that the Department’s inquiry had been fully answered
                        by his telegram No. 332, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>. (File No. 500. A
                        12/72.)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
